{"id":14881458,"mediaExerciseId":"d86e6c36-22ff-4977-b8d5-7de27a26d017","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":489,"solutions":[{"id":5982129,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, we have to find out the coupon payment which we denote with $CP$, where we assume that the face value $F$ is $\\$1,000$ and the coupon rate $CR$ is  $3\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nCP&=F \\times  CR\\\\[7pt]\n&=1,000 \\times 3\\%\\\\[7pt]\n&=1,000 \\times 0.03\\\\[7pt]\n&=\\$30 \n\\end{align*}$$\n\nSo, the coupon payment is $\\boxed{\\$30}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Second, we have to find out the yield to maturity semi- annually by using the excel sheet which we denote with $YTM$, where the number of years $NPER$ ($23\\times 2$) is $46$, coupon payment $PMT$ is $30$, present value $PV$ ($1,000 \\times 1.03)$ is $-\\$1,030$ and the face value we assume $FV$ is $\\$1,000$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nYTM&=RATE(NPER, PMT,PV,FV) \\times 2\\\\[7pt]\n&=RATE(46, 30,-1030,1000) \\times 2\\\\[7pt]\n&=5.76\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the yield to maturity is $\\boxed{5.76\\%}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Finally, let's find out the after-tax cost of debt which we denote with $AC$, where the yield to maturity $YTM$ is $5.76\\%$ and the tax rate $TR$ is $21\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nAC&=YTM \\times (1-TR)\\\\[7pt]\n&=5.76\\% \\times (1-21\\%)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.0576\\times (1-0.21)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.0576 \\times 0.79\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.045\\\\[7pt]\n&=4.5\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the after-tax cost of debt is $\\boxed{4.5\\%}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":fal